# Bilingual Consistency Check (EN/VN/Mixed)

Every time code is modified in chatbot services, verify these rules:

## 1. Keywords MUST have both EN and VN

When adding/editing keyword arrays, dictionaries, or regex patterns:

```csharp
// ❌ BAD — only EN
new[] { "check", "verify", "audit" }

// ✅ GOOD — EN + VN (no-diacritics form)
new[] { "check", "verify", "audit", "kiem tra", "danh gia", "xac nhan" }
```

## 2. String matching MUST strip diacritics

When comparing user input against VN keywords:

```csharp
// ❌ BAD — "tương tự" won't match "tuong tu"
var lower = input.ToLowerInvariant();
return keywords.Any(kw => lower.Contains(kw));

// ✅ GOOD — strip diacritics before comparing
var lower = input.ToLowerInvariant();
var stripped = PromptAnalyzer.StripDiacriticsPublic(lower);
return keywords.Any(kw => lower.Contains(kw) || stripped.Contains(kw));
```

## 3. Training data MUST be bilingual + include samples

When adding training samples to `SelfTrainingService`:
- Every EN sample needs a VN counterpart (and vice versa)
- Conversation chains should mix EN and VN prompts

When adding/changing keywords, intents, categories, or tools:
- MUST add corresponding training samples in `BuildTrainingDataset()` (both EN + VN)
- MUST add at least 1 conversation chain step in `BuildConversationChains()` that uses the new keyword/category

```csharp
// ❌ BAD — added new category keyword but no training sample
CategoryMap: (new[]{"air_handling_unit","ahu","may xl gio"}, "Air Handling Units")
// (no sample in BuildTrainingDataset → self-training won't learn it)

// ✅ GOOD — keyword + matching training samples
CategoryMap: (new[]{"air_handling_unit","ahu","may xl gio"}, "Air Handling Units")
// In AddQuery():
d.Add(new("list all AHU on level 1", Query, "Air Handling Units", new[]{"get_elements"}));
d.Add(new("liệt kê máy xử lý gió tầng 1", Query, "Air Handling Units", new[]{"get_elements"}));
```

## 4. System abbreviations MUST include VN

When adding system abbreviations:

```csharp
// ❌ BAD — EN only
(new[]{"fp","fps"}, "Fire Protection")

// ✅ GOOD — EN + VN
(new[]{"fp","fps","pccc"}, "Fire Protection")
```

## 5. AdaptiveWeightManager keywords MUST come from prompt

When recording learning signals, pass prompt-derived keywords (not tool names):

```csharp
// ❌ BAD — tool name as keyword
AdaptiveWeightManager.RecordSuccess(intent, tc.FunctionName, tc.FunctionName);

// ✅ GOOD — keyword extracted from user prompt
var keyword = ExtractMainKeyword(prompt);
AdaptiveWeightManager.RecordSuccess(intent, keyword, tc.FunctionName);
```

## 6. Evaluate whether to retrain dataset after changes

After modifying any of these, consider running self-training:
- `PromptAnalyzer`: intent keywords, category/system maps, regex patterns
- `ToolCallEnricher`: tool parameter mappings, injection logic
- `ConversationContextTracker`: carryover keywords, carryover logic
- `SelfTrainingService`: training samples, conversation chains

Decision guide:
- **Keyword/regex change only** → Add samples, retrain recommended
- **New category/system/tool** → Add samples + chain steps, retrain required
- **Bug fix in existing logic** → Retrain optional (existing data covers it)
- **New intent type** → Add samples + chains + augmentation entries, retrain required

To trigger retrain: call `SelfTrainingService.RunTraining(epochs: 3, augment: true)` or use the Retrain button in UI.

## Checklist before commit

- [ ] All keyword arrays have EN + VN entries
- [ ] String comparisons strip diacritics for VN
- [ ] Training samples are paired (EN ↔ VN)
- [ ] New keywords have matching training samples in `BuildTrainingDataset()`
- [ ] New features have conversation chain steps in `BuildConversationChains()`
- [ ] System/category abbreviations include VN variants
- [ ] Reference/carryover keywords cover both languages
- [ ] Evaluated if self-training retrain is needed (see Rule 6)
